Several of my friends have done that very thing.  They smoke it at a party and drive home.  Driving under the influence of marijuana is actually less dangerous than driving under the influence of alcohol (note I am not saying either should be done).  Both are INCREDIBLY stupid, yes, and just because I believe it should be a legal drug doesn't mean I think people should go driving under it's influence.  Alcohol is legal, drunk driving isn't, so do the same thing with pot and that solves the whole problem you seemed to have with it being legal.<br>
I do not smoke pot, but I think the drug laws are a bit harsh.  We're talking about a substance that's slightly worse than tobacco.  You can get stuff 2x worse than pot from your neighborhood pharmacy.<br>
Why do I think it should be legal?<br>
Well, as Thorsen said, they could tax the crap out of it and maybe put it to good use.  Even with high taxes, legal pot would be much cheaper than it is now. <br>
Also the real criminals (the mob, big time dealers, whoever else) won't be making as much money if one of the more commonly used drugs was made readily available.  <br>
<br>
And I wouldn't just stop with marijuana, but that's another argument.<br>
